This paper deals with the complexity of reasoning in expressive description logics, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. The use of cardinality restrictions and nominals is a common topic in description logics, which suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.AI and cs.DL. The paper also discusses the use of terminological formalism and predicate logic, which could fall under cs.LO and cs.CC. Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of reasoning, which could be relevant to the subfield of databases (cs.DB).
